<item>
            <title>[CAMEL-8738] Referring to constants using type</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/CAMEL-8738</link>
                <project id="12311211" key="CAMEL">Camel</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Hi,&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;In documentation link &lt;a href=&quot;http://camel.apache.org/simple.html&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;http://camel.apache.org/simple.html&lt;/a&gt; following is written&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Camel 2.11: To refer to a type or field by its FQN name. To refer to a field you can append .FIELD_NAME. For example you can refer to the constant field from Exchange as: org.apache.camel.Exchange.FILE_NAME&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;When I tried it it works. &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;But for example I have class Constants which contain inner class InnerConstants which have a field. I cannot access it from following way.&lt;br/&gt;
${type:Constants.InnerConstants.fieldName}. &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Exception Found: Cannot find class Constants.InnerConstants.fieldName&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Following is the structure of my Constant class&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;class Constants  {&lt;br/&gt;
	public static String test =&quot;Test1234&quot;;&lt;br/&gt;
	public static class InnerConstants &lt;/p&gt;
{
		public static String fieldName = &quot;fieldName&quot;
	}
&lt;p&gt;}&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;My route was:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&amp;lt;route&amp;gt;&lt;br/&gt;
             &amp;lt;camel:from uri=&quot;stream:in&quot; /&amp;gt;&lt;br/&gt;
             &amp;lt;camel:setBody&amp;gt;&amp;lt;simple&amp;gt;${type:Constants.InnerConstants.fieldName}&amp;lt;/simple&amp;gt;&amp;lt;/camel:setBody&amp;gt;&lt;br/&gt;
             &amp;lt;log loggingLevel=&quot;INFO&quot; message=&quot;${body}&quot; /&amp;gt;&lt;br/&gt;
&amp;lt;/route&amp;gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Let me know if you need any other clarification.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment>&lt;p&gt;Windows 7&lt;/p&gt;</environment>
